headline: Rite Aid sells upwards of 1,000 stores to CVS, Walgreens, others
summary: Rite Aid plans to sell the majority of its pharmacies to rival drugstore chains. CVS Health is one of the largest buyers, snapping up prescription files from hundreds of stores and fully acquiring 64 brick-and-mortar locations.
